# Local agent context (private; not committed)
CLAUDE.md

# Gate-round scratch guard: new .review-gate/ / .empanel/ round artifacts are opt-in only
# (`git add -f`) so a careless `git add -A` can't publish local review rounds. Already-committed
# round records stay tracked — gitignore does not affect tracked files.
.review-gate/
.empanel/

# Dogfood spec chains are local process records, not published artifacts (maintainer's call,
# 2026-07-08): new files under docs/specs/ stay uncommitted by default; adding one (a new
# exemplar chain, an ADR) is opt-in via `git add -f`. The already-tracked exemplars and
# overview.md are unaffected — gitignore does not touch tracked files.
/docs/specs/
